Tell Your Story. Help Change the Narrative.
Across the country, anti-LGBTQ+, especially anti-trans, legislation is spreading fear and stigma. Here in Collier County, we’ve seen the ripple effects in rising backlash and efforts to silence our community.
​
Naples Pride is responding with a new storytelling project:
“This Is Us: Get to Know Your LGBTQ+ Community in SWFL.”
Share your story. Because visibility is power, and your voice matters.

About Us
Founded in 2017, Naples Pride is a volunteer-driven, grassroots 501(c)(3) nonprofit dedicated to supporting and celebrating the LGBTQ+ community of Southwest Florida. What began as a “Pride with Purpose” festival to raise funds and visibility has grown into a movement rooted in inclusion, advocacy, and unity.
​
With the support of our vibrant community, we opened The Naples Pride Center in 2020—a safe, welcoming space offering support services, education, social groups, and resources for the LGBTQ+ community and beyond. The Center empowers individuals and families, fosters connection, and inspires meaningful change.
​
Together, we will stand proud, uplift one another, and build a more inclusive future that celebrates diversity in all its forms.
Our Mission
To unite and empower the LGBTQ+community of SWFL, to support, educate and foster equality for all.
Our Vision
Naples Pride will lead & inspire the LGBTQ+ Community of SWFL by providing inclusive programs, events and opportunities utilizing the individual & collective strengths of the community, creating social change and an environment where all feel safe, celebrated & valued.
Support
Help us continue to help our LGBTQ Community. Each donation will go towards our resources to provide programming, counseling, housing and more. We appreciate any and all assistance!

MENTAL HEALTH SERVICES
The Naples Pride Center offers a variety of Support Groups on a regularly scheduled basis.  In addition, we are able to share resources for Mental Health Services, local to Collier County.
​
Every 3rd Tuesday, we welcome adults to our LGBTQ+ Support Group.
​
Every 1st Tuesday and 3rd Tuesday, we welcome all to our Transgender/Non-Binary Support Group.
